HEADWORD: Succula
<hw>Suc"cu*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sucula</ets> a winch, windlass, capstan.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<def>A bare axis or cylinder with staves or levers in it to turn it
round, but without any drum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

